Aim: Study and Implement MVC using Spring Framework
====
Source code:
=========
step1:   click on Spring tool.
===== click on launch.

step2:
====
      click on file->New->Spring Starter Project
      Name: MVC
      type:Marven
      package: Jar
      language: Java
      Version:17
      Group: it
      package :it
     click on next.
     search web on available->click on SpringWeb.Finish.
Step3:
====
   scr/main/java->it(package)->MVCApplication->click on finish.
   Goto it(package)->new->class->Student->Click on finish.
  Goto it(package)->new->class->StudentController->Click on finish.
 Goto src/main/resources->application.properties.
Step 4:
=====

MVC Application:
===========
 package it;
import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;
import org.springframework.boot.autoConfigure.SpringBootApplication;
@springBootApplication
public static void main(String[] args){
     public static void main(String[]  args){
           SpringApplication.run(DemoApplication.class,args);
    }
}
save the file.

Student.java:
=========
   package it;
   public class Student{
            import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;
            public String name;
            public int age;
           public Student(String n,int a){
                 name = n;
                 age = a;
           }
}
Save the file.

StudentController.java:
=================
  package it;
  import org.springframework.web.bing.annotation.GetMapping;
import org.springframework.web.bing.annotation.RestController;
 @RestController
  public class StudentController{
         @GetMapping("/ayaan")
          public Student a(){
                  Student s= new Student("imran",20);
                  return s;  
           }
   }
  Save the file.

Application Properties:
=================
   spring.application.name=MVC
   server.port=8888
   Save the file.

Step 5:
=====
   Right click on MVC->Click on Run as-> click on "SpringBootApp".
//After running goto chrome and search url "localhost:8888/ayyan.

